4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of the algorithms proposed for finding approximate equilibria in different types of games. This falls under the domain of computational complexity, making cs.CC a likely sub-category.
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses concepts from information theory, such as Lipschitz continuity, to provide algorithms for finding approximate equilibria in games. This makes cs.IT a possible sub-category.
